## 04-features/ — Fonctionnalités essentielles

> Activées selon les besoins du projet.

### Backend & données

| Fichier | Rôle |
|---|---|
| `kb-supabase.mdc` | 3 clients (browser/server/admin), env vars, RLS, migrations, Storage, Realtime, types |
| `kb-auth.mdc` | Auth dual (password admin/proprio + magic link tenant), RBAC, middleware, layouts protégés |
| `kb-api-routes.mdc` | Route Handlers vs Server Actions, Zod, rate limit, CSRF, webhooks signés |

> La règle `kb-backend.mdc` (PHP + Express + MySQL) a été supprimée — remplacée par ce trio.

### Applicatif

| Fichier | Rôle |
|---|---|
| `kb-dashboard.mdc` | Admin + espace client — sidebar, assistant-views, CRUD Server Actions, NotificationBell |
| `kb-booking.mdc` | Moteur de réservation — dispo, price engine serveur, sync iCal, confirmation Stripe |
| `kb-cart-checkout.mdc` | Panier Zustand + checkout Stripe — session, webhook signé idempotent, orders |
| `kb-notifications.mdc` | Notifications Realtime (Supabase) + emails transactionnels (Resend) |
| `kb-wishlist-compare.mdc` | Favoris + comparateur — localStorage guest, sync Supabase logged-in, merge au login |

### Transverse

| Fichier | Rôle |
|---|---|
| `kb-forms.mdc` | react-hook-form + Zod + Server Actions, honeypot, UTM, RGPD |
| `kb-seo.mdc` | `metadata`/`generateMetadata`, OG dynamique (`next/og`), JSON-LD, sitemap/robots |
| `kb-image-optimizer.mdc` | `next/image`, Supabase Storage, AVIF/WebP, sizes, priority LCP, blur placeholder |
| `kb-performance.mdc` | RSC, streaming, dynamic imports, `next/font`, cache, revalidate, CWV |
| `kb-security.mdc` | Env vars, RLS, CSRF, CSP headers, rate limit, webhook signatures |
| `kb-error-states.mdc` | `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, skeletons, empty states, boundaries |
| `kb-cookie-consent.mdc` | vanilla-cookieconsent v3, GTM, PostHog, Google Consent Mode v2 |

